  "meta": {
    "package": "@camunda/design-system",
    "import": "import {Select, SelectItem} from '@camunda/design-system';",
    "docs": "# Select\n\nA custom listbox for choosing one option from a list. Use in forms or filters when the user picks a single value from a finite, mutually exclusive set — and you want a styled dropdown rather than the OS-native picker.\n\n## When to use\n\n- **Single-select form field** — compose `Select` + `SelectTrigger` containing `<SelectValue placeholder>` + `SelectContent` with `<SelectItem value>` per option.\n- **Placeholder text** — `<SelectValue placeholder=\"Pick a framework\" />` shows until a value is chosen.\n- **Pre-selected default** — `<Select defaultValue=\"next\">` (uncontrolled) or `<Select value onValueChange>` (controlled).\n- **Grouped options** — wrap groups in `<SelectGroup>` with a `<SelectLabel>` header; separate groups with `<SelectSeparator />`.\n- **Disabled state** — pass `disabled` on `<Select>` (whole field) or on a single `<SelectItem disabled>`.\n- **Compact density** — `<SelectTrigger size=\"sm\">` (the only size variant; default is `default`).\n- **Validation** — set `aria-invalid` on `<SelectTrigger>`; the trigger restyles via the `aria-invalid` selector.\n\n## When not to use\n\n- **Action menu** (callbacks, not values) — use `MenuButton` or `OverflowMenu`.\n- **Multi-select** — use `MultiSelect` or a `ComboBox` with multi mode.\n- **Free-text + suggestions** — use `ComboBox`.\n- **A handful of mutually exclusive options visible at once** — use `RadioGroup`.\n- **Native form serialisation without JS** — render a hidden `<input type=\"hidden\" name>` companion or use a form library.\n\n## Composition\n\n- The trigger is a `<button>`, not a native `<select>` — there is no `name`/`form` integration. Wire up via `react-hook-form`, TanStack Form, or a hidden input.\n- Field labels, helper text, and error messages are **not** built in. Render an external `<label>` and sibling `<p>` for messaging.\n- The dropdown content always portals to `<body>` (via `<SelectContent>`); ancestor `overflow:hidden` will not clip it.\n- Custom rich content inside `<SelectItem>` (icons, badges) shows in the panel but the trigger still displays only the item text.",
    "migrationGuide": "# Select — Carbon → shadcn migration guide\n\n## Underlying primitive\n\n- **Carbon `Select`** wraps a native `<select>` element. Items are real `<option>`s; the dropdown is the OS-native picker.\n- **shadcn `Select`** is a Radix-based custom listbox (`@radix-ui/react-select`). It renders a `<button>` trigger and a Portal'd content panel; no native `<select>` is involved.\n\nThis is the biggest behavioural difference and drives most of the others.\n\n## Structural differences\n\nCarbon's `Select` is monolithic: pass `<SelectItem>`s as children, set `labelText`/`helperText`/`invalidText` on the parent.\n\nshadcn's `Select` is fully decomposed: explicit `<SelectTrigger>`, `<SelectValue>`, `<SelectContent>`, optional `<SelectGroup>` / `<SelectLabel>` / `<SelectSeparator>`, plus `<SelectItem>` per option.\n\n| Concept | Carbon | shadcn |\n|---|---|---|\n| Root | `<Select labelText=\"…\" />` | `<Select>…</Select>` (open state lives here) |\n| Trigger / value | implicit (built-in) | `<SelectTrigger><SelectValue /></SelectTrigger>` |\n| Dropdown panel | implicit (native picker) | `<SelectContent>` (Radix Portal + custom panel) |\n| Item | `<SelectItem value=\"…\" text=\"…\" />` | `<SelectItem value=\"…\">{label}</SelectItem>` |\n| Field label | `labelText` prop | external `<label>` |\n| Helper text | `helperText` prop | external `<p>` |\n| Invalid + error text | `invalid` + `invalidText` | `aria-invalid` + external `<p>`; style trigger via `data-[state]` selectors |\n| Warn state | `warn` + `warnText` | not modeled — render manually |\n| Group / divider | `<SelectItemGroup label=\"…\">` | `<SelectGroup><SelectLabel>…</SelectLabel><SelectItem/>…</SelectGroup>` + `<SelectSeparator />` |\n| Hidden placeholder | `<SelectItem disabled hidden value=\"\" text=\"Pick…\">` (boilerplate) | `<SelectValue placeholder=\"Pick…\" />` (built-in) |\n| Density variants | `size=\"sm\" / \"md\" / \"lg\"` | none — restyle `<SelectTrigger>` via Tailwind |\n| Inline variant | `inline` prop | none — build manually |\n| Light variant | `light` prop | none — set CSS variables |\n| Skeleton | `<SelectSkeleton>` | none — use the generic `skeleton` primitive |\n\n## Carbon features missing in shadcn\n\n- **`labelText` / `helperText` / `invalidText` / `warnText`** — Carbon ships labels and messaging in the field. shadcn forces external composition (typically with the `Field` primitive).\n- **`warn` state** — Carbon distinguishes invalid (red) from warning (amber). shadcn has only `aria-invalid`. Mimic warning by hand-rolling amber classes.\n- **`size=\"sm\"` / `\"lg\"`** — density variants. shadcn's `<SelectTrigger>` is one fixed size; restyle with Tailwind.\n- **`inline` prop** — Carbon's \"inline label\" variant where the label sits beside the trigger. shadcn requires custom flexbox composition.\n- **`light` prop** — Carbon's light-on-dark treatment. shadcn relies on theme tokens; no toggle prop.\n- **`<SelectItemGroup label>`** — Carbon's grouping is one component with a built-in `<optgroup>`-like label. shadcn splits into `<SelectGroup>` + `<SelectLabel>`.\n- **`<SelectItem disabled hidden>` placeholder pattern** — Carbon's idiom for a default/placeholder option. shadcn's `<SelectValue placeholder>` is more elegant.\n- **Native form serialisation** — `<select name=\"…\">` works inside `<form>` without JS. shadcn requires you to add a hidden `<input type=\"hidden\" name>` companion or integrate with a form library.\n- **Native mobile UX** — Carbon delegates to the OS picker on touch devices (much better UX on iOS/Android). shadcn's Radix listbox renders the same custom panel everywhere.\n- **`<SelectSkeleton>`** — Carbon ships a skeleton variant. shadcn has none.\n- **Render-prop `itemToString` / `renderSelectedItem`** — Carbon has hooks for non-string item rendering (e.g., icons next to options); accomplished in shadcn via arbitrary children inside `<SelectItem>`, but the trigger's selected-value rendering is `<SelectValue>`'s `<SelectItemText>` only.\n\n## shadcn features missing in Carbon\n\n- **Custom panel styling** — full control over the dropdown's look (borders, shadows, animations). Carbon's native picker is OS-styled.\n- **Group + separator primitives** — first-class `<SelectGroup>`, `<SelectLabel>`, `<SelectSeparator>` for richer hierarchy.\n- **Per-item rich content** — render icons, descriptions, badges inside `<SelectItem>`. Carbon's native `<option>` is text-only.\n- **Animation primitives** — entry/exit animations driven by `data-state` attributes.\n- **`asChild`-style swap** — swap any sub-component with `asChild` (Radix slot pattern).\n- **Scroll buttons** — auto-rendered `<SelectScrollUpButton>` / `<SelectScrollDownButton>` when the panel overflows.\n- **Position prop** — `<SelectContent position=\"popper\" | \"item-aligned\">` to choose between popper-style positioning (anchored under trigger) or item-aligned (selected item lines up with trigger). Carbon's native picker has no equivalent.\n\n## Behavioural differences\n\n- **Trigger element** — Carbon: native `<select>` with browser-styled chevron. shadcn: `<button>` with custom chevron.\n- **Mobile** — Carbon: native OS picker. shadcn: same custom panel everywhere.\n- **Form integration** — Carbon: `name` attribute serialises automatically. shadcn: needs a hidden input or form-library integration.\n- **Keyboard** — Both support arrow keys, type-ahead, Escape. shadcn additionally supports `data-state`-driven custom focus rings.\n- **Z-index / portal** — shadcn portals to `<body>`; Carbon renders inline (so parent `overflow:hidden` can clip the OS picker, though that's typically a non-issue with native pickers).\n- **Selected-value rendering** — Carbon shows the option's `text`. shadcn shows whatever's inside `<SelectItem>` via `<SelectItemText>` (still text only — no rich content in the trigger).\n\n## Migration checklist\n\n1. Replace `<Select labelText helperText>` with `<Select>` + a sibling `<label>`/`<p>`.\n2. Restructure children:\n   - Wrap the visible trigger value in `<SelectTrigger><SelectValue placeholder=\"…\" /></SelectTrigger>`.\n   - Wrap option list in `<SelectContent>…</SelectContent>`.\n3. Replace `<SelectItem text>` with `<SelectItem value=\"…\">{text}</SelectItem>`.\n4. Drop the `<SelectItem disabled hidden value=\"\">` placeholder; use `<SelectValue placeholder=\"…\" />`.\n5. Replace `<SelectItemGroup label=\"X\">` with `<SelectGroup><SelectLabel>X</SelectLabel>…</SelectGroup>`.\n6. For grouped lists, optionally insert `<SelectSeparator />` between groups.\n7. Replace `invalid` + `invalidText` with `aria-invalid` on `<SelectTrigger>` + a sibling `<p>` for the message; restyle the trigger if needed.\n8. For `warn`: render amber styling by hand — no shadcn primitive.\n9. If the form posts via plain HTML: add `<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"…\" value={selected} />` next to the `<Select>`, or wire up `react-hook-form` `Controller`.\n10. If the surface targets mobile, evaluate whether the OS-native picker matters; shadcn's panel has the same UX on all devices.\n11. Drop `size`, `inline`, `light` props — restyle with Tailwind classes if needed."
  }
